    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix dead code issue in oai_dfts_neon.c by removing extra endif\n\n### Summary\nThe ARM neon DFT implementation contained dead code due to an unmatched preprocessor directive. The file `openair1/PHY/TOOLS/oai_dfts_neon.c` had an extra `#endif` at the end that caused all code following it, including the main test function, to be excluded from compilation on ARM platforms.\n\nThis manifested as the test functions never being compiled or executed when building for ARM targets, even though they were intended to be part of the build. Users attempting to run DFT performance tests on ARM would find that the main function was completely missing from the compiled binary.\n\nThe fix removes the unmatched `#endif` directive, allowing the main function and associated test code to be properly compiled and executed on ARM platforms. This also corrects several indentation issues throughout the file where tabs were replaced with spaces for consistency.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/TOOLS/oai_dfts_neon.c`: Removed extra `#endif` directive at end of file\n- `openair1/PHY/TOOLS/oai_dfts_neon.c`: Fixed indentation inconsistencies (tabs to spaces)\n"
}